EMISSION PROBLEMS FORCE FORD RECALL 
Ford Motor Co. will recall 513,000 cars that exceeed federal emission standards 
for hydrocarbons and carbon monoxide, the Environmental Protection Agency said 
Monday. 
The affected models are the 1984 Ford Escort, EXP and Escort Wagon and Mercury 
Lynx and Lynx Wagon with 1.6-liter engines, the EPA said. About half of the 
1985 versions of the same models will also be recalled. California cars are 
unaffected, the EPA said. 
The repairs involve modification of spark timing, air injection and exhaust-gas 
recirculation to lower engine emissions and improve catalytic converter 
performance. 
